# Ironflyer Studio — environment
#
# Point the studio at a running orchestrator to go live. When unset, the studio
# runs in offline "sample data" mode (no login required).
#
#   1. Run the orchestrator locally (see core/orchestrator + DEPLOY.md).
#   2. Copy this file to `.env` and set the GraphQL endpoint below.
#   3. Restart `pnpm dev:studio`. The sidebar will show "connected" and the
#      login screen will appear — sign in, and chat/dashboard/security go live.
#
# The endpoint is the orchestrator's GraphQL URL (POST). SSE feeds and chat are
# derived from it automatically (the /graphql suffix is stripped for those).
VITE_GRAPHQL_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:8080/graphql

# The embedded IDE + workspace File API live on the runtime service, reached at
# the relative base `/api/runtime`. The Vite dev server proxies that to the
# runtime on :8090 (see vite.config.ts); override the proxy target with the
# RUNTIME_PROXY env when running `pnpm dev`. To bypass the proxy and call a
# runtime directly (e.g. a remote one), set VITE_RUNTIME_URL to its URL.
# RUNTIME_PROXY=http://localhost:8090
# VITE_RUNTIME_URL=
